transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, good morning or afternoon, good morning over here.

Speaker 1: Well, anyway, I'm calling in regards to an order I never received.

Speaker 2: My first name is Aldo, A-L-D-O.

Speaker 1: My last name is Aguilar, A-G-U-I-L-A-R.

Speaker 2: Let's see what's going on with this order, Mr. Aguilar, sit tight.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, and what are you missing, Mr. Aguilar?

Speaker 1: I am missing the Viagra because the testosterone, I did receive it,

Speaker 2: but the Viagra, I never got that in the mail.

Speaker 1: Supposedly it was shipped on the 16th or delivered on the 16th,

Speaker 2: I have here in the tracking, but I just never received it in my mailbox.

Speaker 1: I just never got it.

Speaker 2: So in a situation like this, Mr. Aguilar, the USPS has stated that they've delivered.

Speaker 1: So normally what I would have you do is go through a USPS, call them,

Speaker 2: go through an investigation to see what's the deal, if it was stolen or what have you.

Speaker 1: As a one-time courtesy, this is your first order with us,

Speaker 2: we want to start things out on the right foot.

Speaker 1: I can reship this for you at no cost, of course.

Speaker 2: Is there like a history of theft?

Speaker 1: Will it be okay if I reship it?

Speaker 2: I'm hoping this is just like an it was lost type situation in the mail,

Speaker 1: and usually your mail all gets there.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I mean, there's no history of theft.

Speaker 1: Okay, so it was just a little USPS error, so we'll reship this thing as a one-time courtesy,

Speaker 2: and then we should see it there by the end of the week, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you very much, buddy.

Speaker 2: No problem, and I'll just note down the account here,

Speaker 1: so if anything like this happens in the future, we just have a record.

Speaker 2: And you're all set, Mr. Aguilar.

Speaker 1: All right, thanks a lot, man. You have a good day.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye-bye now.
